      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "88c578bbc250b40a",
      "text": "My ‘container’ (in a psychoanalytic as well as analytic sense?) for such commitments is ‘Six Rs’, six **structures of feeling**, all of which warrant recognition and regard even if they are also ‘fragments’, and any of which can consume an entire lifetime of activist commitment - which, de facto, is a silo. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e91cda51249bf533",
      "text": "These Six Rs are:\n- *Rescue & respite* - A passionate movement of the heart for the succour and defence of people (and non-humans) under immediately present threat to their life, livelihood and comfort, from forces of **fiat**, which must be nullified with *matching* fiat.\n*It mobilises in response to refugees for example, manifests in food banks, in ‘deep green’ actions, in earthquake or tsunami responses.*\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f3a33259c0442106",
      "text": "- *Resistance* - Locally, in a knowable community, establishing a regime of basic alternative means of subsistence and wellbeing under self-determination and through mutual aid, free in some degree from dominant economic and cultural hegemonies, but on the verge of **poverty**, destitution, crushed liberty.\n*It appears in urban farms, food networks, unions, coops; water struggles, responses to ongoing clear-felling, mono-cultural plantation-ism, indigenous fights against oil extraction and the spoil of oil extraction.*\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "53e2d633050e40df",
      "text": "- *Reporting & recording* - Bringing **’news from elsewhere'** . . of how life, resistance and revolution are and were (in history) being conducted, how rescue is and was required, how means were and are mobilised, how reparation and reconciliation are being enacted and were achieved.\n*It appears in investigative journalism and blogging, oral histories, NGOs like Greenpeace or Amnesty.*\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "85f94c60e74e4087",
      "text": "- *Re-weaving* - Intentionally, prefiguratively, assembling a ’new social economy', an operational ecology of use-value **provisioning**.\n*Understood for example to comprise coop startups, community enterprises and B-corps, regional food networks, ‘partner State’ collaborations, circular flows of material and energy ‘within the doughnut’, infrastructures of free software and un-surveilled communications, fair trade, democratic money, community land trusts, peer-to-peer production and exchange.*\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "8a2e04bd6605eda1",
      "text": "- *Reparation & reconciliation* - Securing social (and environmental, and generational, and trans-species; etc) justice, and giving - in fair and full compensation for what has been taken and been refused - under juridical and moral principles. \n*Levelling of playing fields. Mutualising hearts that have been profoundly, historically Othered. Achieving pluriverse under uneven development.** \n\n"
    },
