      "text": "The diversity of such structures of feeling in the mutual sector figures centrally - but tacitly - in Robin’s ‘new social economy’, with its ‘social’ values. But in DaO this is badly mis-identified as a  ‘grant funded economy’. Only a small part of activity in the mutual sector is conducted under explicit funding, let alone grants: and historically, the mutual sector has always been far more than an *economic* phenomenon, or a waged one. Indeed, what is being ‘waged’ in the mutual sector is more characteristically a *war*, than ‘a fair day’s work’. \n"
